    <h3>The Challenge of Staying Switched On</h3>
    <p>When a B2B client brings you on for a project, you don’t just deliver a service. You become a part of their team for the duration of the work. That close integration sets technical professionals apart from nearly every other provider. The day-to-day experience you create for your client shapes not just the outcome of the project, but your ongoing relationship and reputation within their network. More than any website or sales pitch, it’s this consistent professionalism and presence that sets you apart. Twennie’s approach to business development focuses on helping you stay engaged, responsive, and “switched on” in the moments that matter most.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="subs-item">
    <h3>The Project Lifecycle - According to the Client</h3>
    <p>Staying “switched on” means staying engaged with your clients—even when you’re not actively working on a project. In fact, that in-between time can be the most important. For clients, projects are always in motion, even months or years before they break ground. Strong business development isn’t about waiting for RFPs to land. It’s about keeping your ear to the ground, staying visible, and nurturing trust long before the formal competition begins. Showing up consistently and staying attuned (switched on) to your client’s world puts your team in the best position to win—not just through proposals, but through presence.
</p>
